    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-12-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="676" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                <head>No. 674.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Sickles</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-12-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 5,
                                        1873</date>. (Received 7.40 a.m., Dec.
                                6.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your instruction of yesterday received at 10.30 this morning.
                                Interview with minister at 3 this afternoon. He said order sent
                                Wednesday to Polo directed him to consult Minister Soler in Havana
                                about place of surrender, and leave time to be named by you. He said
                                Polo had full authority to act as soon as place should be
                                determined. Minister said, in conclusion, he preferred to let his
                                previous orders stand, but he would direct Polo to lose no time in
                                coming to an understanding with Soler and signing further agreement
                                with you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>SICKLES.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
